function minOperations(nums) {
    let operations = 0;
    for (let i = 1; i < nums.length; i++) {
        if (nums[i] <= nums[i - 1]) {
            let diff = nums[i - 1] - nums[i] + 1;
            operations += Math.ceil(Math.log2(diff));
            nums[i] += diff;
        }
    }
    return operations;
}
```

    We iterate through the array, starting from the second element. If the current element is smaller than or equal to the previous element, we calculate the difference between them and add 1. We then calculate the number of division by 2 operations needed to reach that difference using a logarithm with base 2, and round that number up to the nearest integer (as we're only interested in whole operations). We add the difference to the current element to make sure it's greater than the previous element, and increment the number of operations. We continue this process for the rest of the array, and finally return the total number of operations needed to sort the array in non-decreasing order.

